Ingredients required for the preparation of 100 litre of 1 percent bordeaux mixture are:

1. Copper sulphate 1 kg

2. Quick lime 1 kg

3. Water 100 litres

Dissolve 1kg powdered copper sulphate crystals in 50 litres of water in a mudpot or plastic bucket. In another 50 litres of water, prepare milk of lime with 1kg of quicklime. Pour the copper sulphate solution into the milk of lime, slowly stirring the mixture all the while to get 100 litres of 1% bordeaux mixture. Test the mixture before use for the presence of free copper, which is harmful to the plant, by dipping a polished knife in it. If the blade shows a reddish brown colour add more lime till the blade is not stained on dipping. 100 litres can be used for spraying 50 palms @ 2 litre per palm.

Amrut Pani (Nectar water) The second step is the preparation and use of Amrutpani or Nectar water. We all know that Amrut is the heavenly drink which refreshes the gods and has the power to resurrect the dead. In the same manner my Amrutpani invigorates the living soil and converts a dead soil into a living one. I may add here that while following the above mantra to prepare Amrutpani, I have used the knowledge gained through my experiments and have followed some rules of our Ayurvedic system of medicine. 
Preparation of Amrutpani (Nectar Water) 
200 litres of Amrutpani is needed for one acre of farm land which is prepared as under: 
Material: -	
Quarter kilo ghee (clarified butter) from a desi (indigenous breed ) cow
Half kilo of honey
10 kilo of fresh dung from a desi cow
200 litres of water

Tur plantation
The best drainage of water from the medium to heavy (45 to 60 cm deep) is suitable for tur cultivation. This crop is not good in chopping, wet, saline soil. During the second week of July and the first week of July, when the sowing of the sowing occurs, and after the arrival of the sowing, the sow should be completed. Before sowing, add 5 grams of Trichoderma or two grams of thyroid, 2 gms of carbendazim to the per kg of seeds. After this, the seed group of rhizobium bacterial compound should be processed for every 10 kg seed.
ICPL-87 (120 days) for sowing, AKT-8811 (140 days), BSMR-853 (160 days), BSMR .- 736 (170 days), Vipula (145 - 160 days) These varieties should be selected. When planting inter-culturally, add turmeric (1-2), turmeric to excess sunflower (1-2), tur over soybean (1-3), tur to make more sorghum (1-2 or 1-4), tur (1- 6 or 1-8), tur must be sown in more groundnut (1-3), tur pea more (1-3), tur, more urad (1-2).
For continuous harvesting of the crop, add 45 cm to 10 cm for the earliest preparation of ICPL-87. Keep the distance. AKT-8811 for fun 45 by 20cm Keep the distance. 60 by 20cm for early flowering. Keep the distance. For Vipula, medium 90 duration, 90 by 20 cm Keep the distance.
Because the improved varieties respond well to the fertilizer and water, it is necessary to give the quantity of fertilizers in the right quantity. Five tons of good debris per hectare fertilizer or compost or organic fertilizer per hectare should be spread in the field during the last cultivation. During sowing, 25 kg of nitrogen and 50 kg of phosphorus should be given to 125 kg DAP per hectare.

Filter through double layer of muslin cloth and make the volume to 100 liter
Add 1% detergent (Make a paste of the detergent and then mix it in the spray solution)
Mix the spray solution well and use
